Horacio D. Rozanski

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This biographical article is written like a résumé. Please help improve it by revising it to be neutral and encyclopedic. (March 2017)




Horacio D. Rozanski


Born
c. 1969
Argentina


Alma mater
University of Wisconsin–Eau Claire
University of Chicago Booth School of Business


Occupation
Businessman


Employer
Booz Allen Hamilton


Horacio D. Rozanski (born c. 1969) is an Argentine-born American businessman. He serves as the president and chief executive officer of Booz Allen Hamilton.



Contents


1 Early life
2 Career
3 Personal life
4 References



Early life[edit]
Horacio D. Rozanski was born in Argentina circa 1969.[1][2][3] He earned a bachelor in business administration from the University of Wisconsin–Eau Claire, and a master in business administration from the University of Chicago Booth School of Business.[3][4]
Career[edit]
Rozanski began his career at Booz Allen Hamilton as an intern.[3] He was its Chief Human Officer from 2002 to 2010,[4] and he became its Chief Strategy and Talent Officer in 2010.[1] He also served as its executive vice president from 2009 to 2011, and as its chief operating officer from 2011 to 2014.[4] He has served as its president since January 1, 2014 and as its chief executive officer since January 1, 2015.[1][4] He earned more than US$3.5 million in 2016.[4]
Rozanski serves on the board of directors of the Center for Talent Innovation.[5]
Personal life[edit]
Rozanski is married.[2]
References[edit]



^ a b c "Booz Allen Executive Leadership: HORACIO D. ROZANSKI PRESIDENT AND CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER". Booz Allen Hamilton. Retrieved March 23, 2017. 
^ a b Rozanski, Horacio D. (January 5, 2014). "Horacio D. Rozanski’s journey from Argentina to the top of Booz Allen Hamilton". The Washington Post. Retrieved March 23, 2017. 
^ a b c Small, Vanessa (January 6, 2014). "Behind the career: Horacio D. Rozanski". The Washington Post. Retrieved March 23, 2017. 
^ a b c d e "Booz Allen Hamilton Holdings: Horacio D. Rozanski". Bloomberg. Retrieved March 23, 2017. 
^ "About Us: Board of Directors". Center for Talent Innovation. Retrieved March 23, 2017. 






